caption: I normally don’t do many online reviews but I’d be remiss not to take the opportunity to toss out 5 well deserved stars. We’ve been there a number of times since Big8 opened and have brought family and friends. Best BBQ in SWFL, hands down, and best brisket I’ve found since leaving Texas. Tried every meat so far and it’s all top shelf, perfect smoke on everything. Everyone loved the smoker style serving cart. Great idea and no worries about getting served a cold meal. Keep up the good work.
Amazing food, very friendly and great customer service.

Food is ok. However, it is overpriced. $8 for a single small sausage link without a drink or side. Same with brisket - a single slice is available for $10. I ordered from Grubhub twice, and in both cases, the actual food is half the size shown or advertised in the picture. Very deceiving and frankly a scam/ripoff. I can't recommend it.
Great BBQ, pulled pork was my amazing.

Cool place and great food (lots of fantastic choices)! The sides are amazing as are the well crafted meats. We got (3) 3 meat choice combos and were very pleased! We look forward to our next visit and the leftovers tomorrow  😋
Absolutely delicious! The brisket and pulled pork was sooo juicy! The flavor was so good I really didn't even want to use the sauces. Will definitely be back.
Brisket was good, but portion size is too small. When you pay $10 you'd think they would give you more.

OMGOSH!!  I got a full rack of ribs.  I got 3 meals out of it.  It must be a 3lb slab.  Each rib was HUGE!!   The meat was really tender and tasted great without any sauce.   I had garlic mac and cheese, too die for!!!  I also got the Big 8 baked beans, big chunks of meat in them, delicious!  I  also got a corn muffin, it was as big as a baseball!  The staff was great.  I will DEFINITELY be going back.
Great food, friendly service and good prices. What more could you ask for?
Great burnt ends must get there early for the burnt ends that usually out by 5. Love the brisket love the 8 cheese mac and cheese!
Food is awsom
Out of half of items at dinner time.  What we ordered was ok.  Was just set on having something which they did not have.
awsome food awsome food.will be back very soon

OMG!! Best barbecue platter we've ever had! And, the side dishes are off the charts as well. Very unique flavors/sauces and delectable garnishes (pickled red onions -- my favorite). Not your average-tasting barbecue dishes -- moist, tender, scrumptious. Great customer service and generous portions. These folks obviously care about their patrons. Please add Big 8 BBQ to your list of dining pleasures!
Tender tasty brisket and baked beans very good.  Price for supper OK. Rather pricey for lunch though.
Great food! Will return.
Delicious meal with generous portions...great sauces. Better try them all!
Great food, great service!!
Well..... It ain't "The Shed" in Mississippi.... But it's good! Collards and Mac and cheese were awesome
Great place
Great food! I love BBQ and this did not disappoint. My server Amy was also awesome!

Food was delicious, staff couldn't have been more friendly.  Macaroni (garlic and regular) delicious.  Restaurant very clean, welcoming, and quick courteous service. Value, however, low.  I was disappointed with the portion size for double meat portion of brisket ends.  I can empathize with challenges for restaurant owners during pandemic.  Still, I would have rather the cost be a few bucks more with a decent portion size.  We left hungry.  Great food otherwise.
Home of the liquid smoke. And soggy potato salad ... rather get bbq from 7/11
Burnt End brisket is amazing
Food was good could be hotter.... Owner and staff very friendly
Great food and service.
Great BBQ!!! Staff was excellent
Great food,  fast friendly service
Too expensive for the small portions you get.
Great place nice people excellent BBQ. Best baked beans in the cape
OK, just had the brisket and burnt ends. This is by far the best barbecue I've had and I used to live in Memphis, Dallas and Atlanta. Will I be going back? Hell yeah!

As a chef for 20 years, I’m picky when it comes to food. They are doing a wonderful job here. The pulled chicken is very delicious and tender. Of course the cornbread is amazing and one of my favorite things to cook his macaroni and cheese so I’m very picky when it comes to that and they did an awesome job, very good and last but not least the Kansas City sauce is straight 🔥 🔥🔥🔥🔥🔥 you can put that on anything and it’ll make it taste good. Keep up the good work guys.

Went to big 8 the other day. Thought I'd give it a try. Ratings were good. So I ordered a couple of combo platters.  Ribs, brisket, pulled pork, baked beans and Mac and cheese. Walked in. Looked a little like an assembly  line corporate  restaurant. Started to get nervous. My order was ready, took it home to eat. Fantastic....by far the best  BBQ I have ever eaten. The ribs were so juicy and fall off the bone. Brisket and pork the same way. Light smoke ring, very juicy. Baked beans out of this world and Mac and cheese like you have never had before. Very cheesy like a pizza. This is my new goto place for BBQ. Dont tell everybody needs to be kept a locals secret. 5 plus stars. They could not have done any better. Big portions also.
Definitely come try this restaurant/bar. The food is absolutely amazing, the staff and owners are so nice. Come and give it a try and you'll be back time and time again.

Best BBQ I've literally ever had! This is a small business that has only been open for about 3 months! If I were you I'd go there now before the wait to get a table is crazy long! The staff are super nice and helpful. They taking a carving station right to your table and carve the meat right there in front of you. So, not only are you getting delicious food you are also getting a fun experience! I recommend any meat on the menu, but do not leave there without trying the mac and cheese! I never like anyone's mac and cheese...ever. This is phenomenal! Try this place out asap! Cant wait to go back!!

Visited here for the first time today and was blown away! Such a cute place inside and loved the music 🎶 Huge booths to sit in We had pulled pork Pulled chicken 8 chz Mac n chz Potato salad 8baked beans (had brisket in them) Corn bread (honey butter) And some craft beers. Everything was amazing. They also said at dinner time they come to your table to slice the meat fresh in front of you 🤤 Can't wait to go back!
Great food. Brisket sausage awesome. Garlic mac and cheese to die for. I dont think there's anything that isn't great. Aj  great service.

I’ve been a lot of places and had a lot of bbq and this is flat out some of the best I’ve ever had. The Brisket is on point each and every time I’ve had it. Not to mention the staff is friendly, not the least of which, Pit Master Bill. Come and bring your appetite.

Thank you for responding to my husband post and delete after reading it. Donald Moyer is my husband and we were there with our family thinking everything was going to be good and we found out that it wasn't. You said that the manager came to our table, the only two that came to the table  Was the awkward meet card and our server. We were displeased with your barbecue. We are a family with little children that needed high chairs or tables when even accommodate for that they were too high. Your servers never adjusted to accommodate our family.  And for you to delete a negative post is very unprofessional on your part. Let see how long this stays on Google.

For the money, it's just okay. $17 brisket combo, one slice of meat? Over priced. The meat was dry with the exception of the fat. The "gingerbread cornbread was good. The beans were good. No fountain drinks or brewed sweet tea either. Who serves BBQ with no sweet tea?  Must be a northerner owner! It's a one-time visit for us.  If you are looking for a better bbq IMO go to Smoking Pit BBQ in North Ft Myers.  >> Replying to board member reply to my review.  Unfortunately you must be mistaken us for some other patron. The server who served us was on his first day as an employee and no manager stopped by our table to ask anything. The only people who spoke to us was the seating hostess and the waiter.  When we asked for sweet tea he said you only have bottled or soda cans. We even asked for brewed tea and he said no.  A couple of other issues noted from other tables around us. On the menu, the "sausage brisket" the waiter had to explain this concept numerous times when a couple was ordering the 2 meat combo. The waiter was terrible at explaining it. When their meals were brought to their table the husband said to the wife "that's it, this place is way over priced for what you get". Since I had already thought the same when my meal was delivered it stuck with me.  We weren't offered sauce, another drink or anything else until we were sitting there waiting for the waiter to walk by and he asked us do we want our check. I jokingly told him, no not really. And he started fiddling with the handheld machine.  Then going to pay. The waiter had a terrible time tearing off the receipt from the machine. On the receipt it has the QR code to scan...ONLY compatible with iPhones. This cuts out 60-70% of the population since iPhones are only approximately 30% of the cell phone user market. The little nuances just kept building up...  The dark black high walled dining table terrible design. Feel like you're eating in a box. Our joke was "they" dont want customers to see the other customers disappointment when they receive their meals.  The colors are gaudy. First impression walking in was were we at a NE fish market. It too was a turn off.  The outdoor seating would have been nice but the afternoon sun was cooking the painted black wood furniture with no shade.  Again, must be a North Easterner thought. If you have outdoor seating, you MUST have shade! And black furniture on black asphalt... come on!  You haven't actually ate lunch at noon outside on a sunny day at this location have you? Good idea, terrible execution.  I hope these insights help you out but as you know reviews can make or break a business.  Our first experience at Big 8 BBQ was not worth returning. Maybe when reviews state the place has changed for the better then we will bring our money and network but until then I wish you the best of luck.

We had no idea what to expect, but this place is exceptional! They bring a cart right to the table and prepare the meat. Even my picky eater nephew said the food is "phenomenal". I'm glad we took the chance to try a new BBQ place!
Big 8 is the best BBQ in the state by far.

To many things here wrong, this BBQ was to KC driven not my region style BBQ. I was put off by the meat cart, very very awkward you should rethink that there. You can mess up greens so many ways and they did it. Seen the reviews that made us go, but won't be back.
They served nice smoky pork an amazing corn muffin
In love!! Will be back with my crew. Every thing was top notch.
Large portions. Food was delicious. I will be back.
AMAZING food! Great service
Incredible as always! Continue doing what you do best, BBQ!
Big eight BBQ downtown cape Coral don't miss it

The BEST barbeque ever! We have eaten here 3 times and the food has always been amazing.  The chefs bring the food out in a cart and cut the meat fresh at your table.  Our out of town guests were so amazed and will definitely be back.   Not a fancy sit down restaurant but definitely 5 stars!
Great service and food looking forward to going again
Attentive service and clean.  No fries, sides were not my style, pulled pork was dry.  Probably won't be going back when I want BBQ.

Being from Kansas City we were anxious to try this BBQ from KC. We had a 3 meat combo with brisket, pulled pork and burnt ends. Also sides of garlic mac and cheese and the bbq beans. We loved it all. The burnt ends were my favorite of all 3 then brisket. The sauces they had were KC, Memphis, Texas, and NC. We had the KC and Memphis (hot). Both were good a little to thin for us. They have a variety of beverages including cocktails and beer. I would definitely recommend this place for good bbq!
Some really good BBQ!  Had the brisket and burnt ends combo with Big8 beans and coleslaw.  The meats were tender and delicious, the beans were full of brisket as well.  Awesome!
Best we've tasted so far in Florida.  We'll be back.
Food was delicious and our waitress was great!!
Excellent food, great service!

had dinner tonight,  welcomed by Kevin at the door  w/humor  and offered us a drink at the bar where we met  Mel (that's what her friends call her) gave a history of the place and a drink w/Mr Toms Distill  products. We then were served table side the best meats and side I have ever eaten.  If you haven't been your missing out.  don't eat the after dinner mint  LOL(ask Amy)
BOMB food! This place is definitely now our go to BBQ spot Mathew was super helpful when explaining the menu, he was very warm and welcoming! 10/10 would recommend Big 8
Quick and easy pick up, delicious food!

We have gotten take out from Big 8 several times. Hands down, they have the best smoked brisket anywhere in Southwest Florida, it is always tender and juicy. Always fresh never left over from the day before. All their sides are fantastic. Even the employees are friendly and five star! You can't go wrong here.
Good place

Decided to stop by after driving past it the last couple of months.  Excellent food.  The service was very, very good.  The sausage is made with brisket - no pork goes into it.  I had that and the pulled chicken.  The Texas baked beans and garlic mac were excellent too and definitely home made.  I will also point out that you can trust the heat level indicated on a given sauce..  When they say something is spicy hot - it is.  So many restaurants will say something is spicy and it doesn't even register.  Here the heat level matches to what they tell you on the menu.  I know I will definitely be back many times over.  I have been saying for years that Cape Coral needs a good BBQ restaurant and now it has one!
Great bbq! Texas beans are probably the best I've ever had and the garlic Mac & cheese is outstanding
The food was good and the service was excellent.
Great food. Went way out of their way to be of service .  Excellent prices
BBQ has no need for sauce... taste so good!!!
The brisket is fantastic, and so is the chicken. Their sauces are HOT so taste in advance!
Just my opinion. If you like the taste of liquid smoke ? Than this is the place for you .. And stay clear of the smoked potato salad. Not really sure what that is with the soggy potatoes !!!
Very good bbq, but go relatively early because the food sells out. Collard greens are amazing.
Best BBQ around ! Melts in your mouth and great flavor!

Good Lord. Best pulled pork and brisket I've ever had. The burn on the brisket is perfect and bursting with flavor. The pulled pork is so moist and delicious, I could lay in it. I hope this place always has a line wrapped around the corner. Better than anything I've had in the southeast. Great job guys! Smoke on
Great Place .. the food was fantastic  service was excellent and the prices are very reasonable. I highly recommend this place ... wish they had a place in Michigan.
Best BBQ in Cape Coral for sure. Owners have a very high standard of meat and technique. Great flavor, atmosphere and prices. Can't say enough about it, its that good.
Excellent service and wonderful food.

Today was our first visit to Big 8 BBQ and we were so glad we decided to give it a try! We had the half chicken with sides of Big8 beans (amazing!), cole slaw, and collard greens. The portions are huge! The chicken is moist and doesn't have that heavy smoke flavor. Perfect!  All we can say is you better be hungry because you will get plenty of delicious, flavorful food! We plan to do take out for our next family get together.
Amazing food, excellent service, and great experience! Do yourself a favor and come eat here!
Excellent food, service and all around  great experience, I recommend this place anytime you are hungry.
Big 8 BBQ knows how to smoke meats! Incredible food, and service!

New owners doing a great job to make customers comfortable and happy.  Delicious food,  lots of it has hot spices but not to hot. Give them a try. You will be glad you did. Go early so they won't run out of what you might want. They are still learning how much to prepare each day.
Everything was top notch. I haven't tried everything on the menu yet... but in due time.

Decided to try this place for lunch today. I'm really picky about bbq places because there's not a lot around here that do bbq right. I come from a family of competition bbq guys and I do a lot of smoking myself.  Big 8 BBQ is legit! Bbq done right! I had the 3 combo..brisket, pulled chicken and ribs with the big 8 bbq beans and smoked potato salad. Everything was awesome. They're right you don't need any sauce for their meat but if you like it they have some great sauces. Highly recommend! Can't wait to go back.
Excellent BBQ.  Would highly recommend to anyone that loves a amazing BBQ.
Awesome food, great staff! Stuff put me in a food coma!!! Seriously good bbq!!
Walked in people were very amazing always checked on us. The food was amazing over beyond amazing words cant say how amazing this place is. You must try it. Will definitely be coming back soon..
Food  was delicious  service  was outstanding  unique  experience  everyone  was extremely  pleased
Great food Very friendly staff
This was the Best BBQ I have ever had. I am stuffed. Like the name states you get 8 choices of meat, 8 choices of sides. I had the pulled pork, big 8 beans, and coleslaw. Yummy
best bbq i’ve ever had in florida. delicious sides and meats. staff is super friendly and informative and they have a lot of seating options.

Had an incredible lunch today here. Most places will be great at one thing and lacking in another but Big 8 has mastered it all. Burnt ends were amazing, pulled pork was moist and so was the brisket which almost always is dry. Comes with 2 sides and we tried the smoked potato salad, cole slaw and an additional corn bread muffin, I honestly couldn’t pick a favorite as all 3 were perfect. Same goes with all the sauces, full of flavor but definitely on the spicier side. Check them out and wear your stretchy pants.
First time here, FANTASTIC!!! Very COVID cautious, great food, and great people! Best BBQ in the Cape!
Food was delicious. Staff was even better. Super friendly, and so accommodating. We will definitely be back!
Run don’t walk to Big 8..everything and I mean everything was excellent!

Big 8 BBQ is the best BBQ joint I've been to in Florida... and I love good BBQ. The hardy portions of meat are very flavorful and moist. They smoke the meats just right.  My favorite is the brisket and it just melts in your mouth.  The 4 different sauces are each uniquely tasteful and you can tell the kitchen puts just as good care in preparing their sides.  My favorite is the collard greens.  Both the owners, Bill and Kevin and the bar tenders, Rach and Mel, are so friendly.  I like to sit at the bar and they make it the kind of place where it's very comfortable to go to even by yourself. Big 8 BBQ is my new "Go To" Place - especially when I've got visitors in from out of town.  I hope this place is around for a long time and does very well!
Really enjoyed the experience.   The food was AMAZING, the staff was attentive, and the atmosphere was fun!  Can't wait to go back!!
The food is absolutely fantastic!
Amazing food! We tried almost everything and can't wait to come back. Prices are reasonable, service great too!!
Good barbeque... They sell out early so need to order early

Finally true bbq in the cape!  Thus place is awesome!  Great staff and the food is high above the rest!  The brisket and burnt ends are the best.  If you like bbq you have to try this place.  You won't be dissapointed.
Brisket has excellent flavor.  Juicy and does not need added sauce.  Baked beans and mac n cheese are awesome too.
Outstanding food!

One star to get management attention...Great food....BUT .. they need to rethink their “open to 11 or until their food runs out”. Been there 4 times now avg time of arrival  7:30 -8:00.  Out of the good stuff.... especially ribs.   Do I need to reserve my food at 5-6 pm?? Shouldn’t have to do that.... hope they can figure out their food logistics.  Not everyone eats dinner at 5-6 pm ...
OMG!!!!!!! Do not pass this place by! Clean , safe and food is DELICIOUS! Trust a fat guy that loves good food!
Great food! Website is a mess right now. But the meat is great!
Great BBQ! The collard greens and Mac and cheese were out of this world. Can’t wait to go back.
Brisket was melt in your mouth tender-no knife needed!

Big 8 BBQ is awesome.  My husband & I sat at the bar with Rachel, the bartender, who made delicious margaritas!  I had the burnt ends, 8 chez mac & chez & smoked potato salad; my husband had a pulled pork sandwich with coleslaw and Big 8 baked beans.  Everything was top notch!  We will definitely be back!  Nice to meet Kevin & Bill & wish you much success!
Brisket brisket brisket..To me the Ribs were not bad kinda tough I like them falling off the bone but that brisket was just amazing.. I will be back for more brisket you have to try it..

First time in.. will not be our last! We made an effort to try almost everything on the menu. Nothing disappointed. I can’t say enough about their brisket sausage...  and I’m not even a brisket fan! From sauces to sides..  and the meat being the show stopper. Excellent job Big8...  excellent!! See u soon!!!
Came here for my first time and the next week came again for my second! You walk in and it immediately smells AMAZING. Very friendly and funny staff! Love this place so much!! New bbq spot for sure
I've been here 3 times now and I plan on returning over and over again. This place is legit!!!!
Great food
The food was fantastic! They helped with any questions. The service was over the top! You have to give it a try. It's the real deal.

I am thrilled to have found Big 8 BBQ. This is genuine "over the top" slow smoked perfection on a plate. The brisket is by far the star of the show, akin to some of the best i've personally experienced sampling my way across Austin, TX.  But don't get me wrong, the pulled pork, burnt ends, and smoked chicken will leave you wanting more than you could ever eat.  It takes incredible discipline not to eat here every day.  Once you've indulged your BBQ cravings at Big 8, your expectations of smoked meaty delicacies will rarely be exceeded.
The food was awesome, and the service was even better!  Loved the collard greens and garlic Mac-n-cheese.  The ribs were amazing!  We will be back!
Cole slaw and brisket were really good.
Best BBQ I’ve had since Nashville TN. Good job Big8
Absolutely delicious 😋😋

Highly recommended - I think I was sold the moment I heard all of the bbq sauces were made from scratch. I have never tasted all of the flavors I had tonight;  truly original and made from scratch. Between the brisket, Texas and Big 8 beans, garlic Mac and cheese, slaw, and potato salad (yes, I tried these all at one meal).  Aside from the delicious food, the staff was AMAZING! We sat at the bar with Mel (hey!) - she took good care of us and gave great recommendations. All the staff were wearing masks and hustling to feed all the hungry people coming through the door (and it was busy!). So happy to have this new restaurant in the Cape.

Friendly staff, food was amazing and full of flavor. Owner was very friendly and helped us understand the menu and the many different varieties of meats and sides. Loved how we were treated more like family than another customer. Highly recommend to anybody in Cape Coral wanting an amazing barbecue experience. I will definitely be back here soon.

we went there for the first time.. they started serving lunch.. well i had high expectations.. and guess what.. this place knocked it out of the park.  We were both totally impressed.  The staff was friendly and accomodating, and the food was out of this world.  the brisket is by far the best i have ever had, we also had the rib bowl, which was amazingly tasty.  One of the owners came out to see how we were doing,   so basically, this place is great, i felt at home, and the food was great.  this will be our new "go-to" place.
Very tasty BBQ...and the Mac an cheese is amazing
The best baked beans I've ever had in my life! Great customer service as well!! My new favorite lunch spot.

I had the best meal I have had since living in Cape Coral last night. I grew up on bbq and I have never had bbq so good as it was here. I didn’t even add sauce. The sides were excellent too. Can’t wait to go back. The whole vibe here was great. Our server was so genuine with his love of working here and how great the owner is.  This was confirmed later when the owner stopped by our table to talk. Amazing experience and food at Big 8.
Amazing service.  Great food. Definitely will come back.
Best of the best wow. I smoke meat every weekend...These guys know what there doing.
Brisket was very good..Friendly staff..return trip for sure..
Finally a great BBQ place in the Cape!

What are you waiting for?! This place is amazing! Everyone that works here is very friendly and the food??! Where do I begin? Garlic Mac & Cheese, Corn Bread, Big8 Beans...I had Burnt Ends - my first time, and certainly not my last!!! So excited to have this nearby 🤩
From the Kansas City area where there are many BBQ restaurants and I would put this place up against them !! Will be going back for more .

I was not prepared for how amazing the bbq sauces are. I couldn’t stop saying “omg omg omg” the bbq sauces enhanced the flavor of the meat. Very quick pick up time and good packaging. Great prices! Fed my family of 3 for less then 50$! We will be back!

Food was wonderful! We're new to FL from Texas and our first 2 bbq experiences here have been lackluster/dissappointing to say the least. The sides were phenomenal. The greens...rival what you'd find at the best soul food restaurants, tender with a touch of heat.  Makes you feel like you're at home. The 8 cheese Mac was super cheesy and the BBQ beans had almost as much meat as beans! The ribs were falling off the bone, and the brisket sausage was outstanding with a flavor unlike any other sausage. The burnt ends were delicious. The brisket was moist and has that smoke ring you look for in good BBQ.  A great staff can compliment a great meal. As first timers, they explained all the options, offered samples, and recommendations. They checked on us several times throughout our meal. We have been feeling homesick considering the food we've had here, but as long as we can make the occasional pilgrimage to Big 8, I think we'll be just fine.

This place is amazing!! Finally a BBQ place in Cape, AND it’s worth every cent! Melany, the assistant manager and bar tender is phenomenal and Kevin is so hospitable and kind! It’s a great experience from the staff to the flavors. A must in the downtown Cape Coral area!!

There is simply no other BBQ after you taste this.  The service was impeccable, the food came out quickly, and the cocktails were phenomenal as well.  This place smokes their bbq fresh daily, so you may find that certain items have run out if you dine later.  However, the fresh factor and flavor is undeniably superior as a result.  You can choose tableside service where they literally carve the meat selection in front of you, a bar top experience or a quick carry out option.  No matter how you choose to experience this delicious menu, rest assured that you will be greeted with a friendly, attentive staff who create a real down home feel inside the restaurant.  The brisket is the best I have ever had.  Not to mention the garlic mac n cheese and spicy collard greens.  This is serious down home cookin'. Private events and catering options are also available.  Highly recommend.
Hands-down the best barbecue I have ever had! The 8 cheese mac & cheese is to die for!The owners are super nice, and all of the staff are very helpful! Super great service! Can’t wait to go back!!!

I have had a lot of Bbq in my days and this place is by far the best bbq I’ve ever had! The staff is very friendly! My favorite is the collard greens best I’ve had since my mother’s kitchen. The ribs are fall off the bone good and you can’t leave without ordering their creamy delicious garlic mac! I recommend this place if you want some real bbq!
Had a great Sampler plate. The ribs looked great but I thought $24.99 for a rack of spare ribs was too expensive. Maybe if they were Baby Back but spareribs no.
Awesome food. Had a wonderful time
They catered the grand opening of Botanical Brewing Company with pulled pork. I was very impressed with the wood smoke flavor and the sauces. We don’t live in the Cape, but it will be worth the trip.
Went there for the first time today will never go anywhere else EVER again!! The nicest staff and the food was AWESOME!!  Bye Bye rib city!!🍻👍

Excellent, moist, and flavorful tableside bbq dishes. We had bbq chicken, burnt ends, macaroni and cheese, smoked potato salad, and collard greens. Everything was fresh and hot. We met the owners and they are super friendly! I definitely recommend Big 8 BBQ for an authentic bbq dinner.
Disappointed in this restaurant but they are new and hopefully will get better. We had burnt ends and the sampler and both needed help.
Food was very good. Everyone had on masks. Owner stopped by to check on us. We’ll be back

The food was awesome! The brisket was smokie, fork tender and tons of dark bark! Pulled pork was tender and smokey with lots of bark mixed in. Beans and slaw were great too. Staff was friendly and helpful. Its about time that we have great barbecue on the cape!

BIG 8 BBQ Simply Big flavors. Amazing food. Something that needed to happen in the Cape Coral area. Will definitely come back. Everything was delicious. From the brisket to the burnt ends. But those Spicy Baked Beans were out of this world!!

This food is outstanding!!! I had the Two Meat Combo. I chose the brisket and ribs. The brisket has a rub on it unlike anything I have ever tried. Didn’t even need the sauce (which was also delicious). The ribs just fell off the bone. I decided on the garlic Mac and could’ve eaten a tub of it! Finally the baked bean...yum!!!! Highly recommend sitting down for service, as opposed to sitting in the bar. This way the server carves the meat right in front of you!
The smoked turkey was a perfect choice for Thanksgiving! Everyone loved it and even had some for leftovers. We’ll definitely be back for more!!!
Glad we finally have a local BBQ in Cape Coral.   It's just finger lick'n  Good!!!!
Best bbq in the area!
Amazing food!  Hit the spot for BBQ!  The brisket, pork and chicken are delicious and so are the sides. Order all the sides!  Awesome staff. We will be back!

Some damn good BBQ! We ordered via DoorDash and absolutely loved it! Brisket, pulled pork and sausage were awesome! I somehow forgot to order ribs but we’re definitely getting a rack next time! Burnt ends were sold out which was the only bummer. The Texas BBQ beans are everything. So good I’ll need to order 5 sides to save next time! Great Mac and cheese and smoked cornbread, too. Wasn’t expecting this great of BBQ outside of Texas! Just wishing they had a Thanksgiving meal we could order!

I wish i was able to give this 10 stars! Everything about this place is fantastic! The service is phenomenal, the staff is remarkable and the food is beyond amazing! Kevin, the owner,  is so great! He stops by to talk and makes sure everything is to our liking and he is so welcoming and sweet! It's like no other place we have ever experienced!!!! It's a MUST!! A+++++😁

11 out of 10. The food was absolutely amazing, the collard greens are made the correct southern way, Brisket was easily shredded and overall just amazing. The women behind the bar Melanie was wicked nice and energized. Everyone was friendly and generally cared if you enjoyed everything! My new favorite spot!
Best bbq in Cape Coral. Their Brisket is amazing. Great customer service and great food 😊

All I can say is everything is incredible. Super friendly staff and everything is clean and all the food is amazing!! The owner comes around and checks with you to make sure everything is alright which is very rare in establishments. Love how they carve the food right at your table.

The food was great, cannot deny that. It's real smoked food; not the bbq/smoked food they try to pass here in the Cape as bbq.  This would be the only restaurant that can get an A+ for good smoked meat & sides. I even thought the location was good. My only issue was the prices. Menu prices were not the same as in-restaurant prices. There was a $7 increase. The 3 meat combo is $15 but when i couldn't place the order online (i was told the "switch wasn't turned on") & went directly to the restaurant, the 3 meat combo was $22. Not exactly sure why that was & no, I didn't ask. I just ordered the 2 meat combo-- which also refected a different price compared to online ordering. Portion sizes aren't big at all, except for the quarter chicken. My son said that was the best he had ever tasted, even back in KC.
Meat was good. Sauces were spicy even the collards were too hot. I ask for the Kansas and the Memphis I usually mix traditional and spicy but Kansas was a little too spicy on its own

Bland brisket that lacked any kind of smoke flavor, and severely under seasoned. Inedible sauce. Tasted more like a cirporate chain place than anything. Rude staff.  Credit card machine wouldn't work unless I left a tip, and I did take out. Don't particularly like being forced to tip on take out either.
Food service were excellent will be back to try new items

THE GOOD: Big 8 BBQ is simply amazing. Best BBQ I have eaten in years. When we walked in, we were greeted and seated at a table and then explained ordering process. You basically order directly from a cart. I thought this was going to be a little strange; but now I see its genius. You can actually look at the food before you order and ask for more of this or more of that. It is way better than ordering from a menu. After ordering way too much food, I tried the brisket sausage. It was the moistest sausage I have ever seen. I then tried the burn ends. They were amazing! All toasty on the outside but still soft on the inside with just the right amount of fat. Finally, I tried the brisket. My love for the sausage and burnt ends became a distant memory. The brisket is without a doubt the best I have had and after living in Texas for 20 years I have certainly eaten my share of brisket. It is simply fantastic. I realized that everything else was just a tease. The brisket is the main event. My wife said she couldn’t eat her last rib. So, I tried a few bites. As it should, the meat pulled from the bone with just a slight hesitation but once free, was juicy, tender and flavorful. Lastly, even though I am not sure how I was able to eat it, the mac and cheese is crazy creamy and cheesy, the corn bread is fresh and the butter has just a hint of honey. After slouching down in the booth in my meat coma, the owner Kevin came by and noticed we might be needing a nap. He was genuinely nice, super interested in making sure we had a good experience.  THE BAD: Here in lies a problem with Big 8. The brisket is so good, that without taking photos, you cannot remember anything else. Yeah, it is that good. As a nitpick, the benches for the tables are a little tall. My toes could touch the ground by my heals had to dangle. The seat also needs to be a little lower to make the gap between the table and the bench taller because you are stuck in the seat after eating so much. Next, the parking is a pain. We had to park across the street and walk over. After eating so much, it is a long walk. Maybe they can use a valet service and I would not have to walk at all. Hum?  In the end, I highly recommend trying Big 8. I know I will certainly be back!
One of the best BBQ places I’ve been to. Food was amazing and service was excellent from beginning to end. Highly recommend the brisket and garlic Mac n cheese! We will definitely be back!
Food and service was amazing highly recommend Big 8 BBQ!
Fantastic food Smokey pulled pork, delicious brisket, as good as it gets. Tasted homemade just like bbq should be. 10/10

Very first time here. it was off the charts good. The barbecue was delicious the smoked potato salad was unbelievable. So nice to see local supporting locals and Mr. Tom spirits - what an incredible drink menu. Our waiter Will was also amazing. Will be back many times
The best BBQ ever! We will return.

We really loved the whole unique experience. The meat was perfect. Carved tableside. We had brisket, burnt ends, ribs and pulled pork. All very flavorful! The sides were all very good - we are picky when it comes to coleslaw, greens and baked beans. They were all so good. We also had the garlic mac and cheese. Yum! The portions were really generous. 4 sauce choices. We got the regular Kansas City, which was yummy! We didn't get the cornbread, but I would have gotten some grilled Texas Toast if it was on the menu. Would be a great addition to the menu eventually! The special little wet naps at the end was a nice touch. The place was VERY clean and orderly. So were the restrooms. The staff was very helpful, friendly, clean and wearing masks.  The tableside checkout was easy peasy. Pics were after we started eating. Look at the size of that brisket and ribs - Flintstone-ish....lol. Oh - and I lovedlovedloved the pickles and pickled onions on the plate. I'd like the onion recipe and my sister will be picking up coleslaw for Thanksgiving! They also have seating options. Outside, booths, tables and takeout.
Absolutely delicious, everything we tried was so good. And the people are so nice and friendly, location is nice and clean and we enjoyed seating outside. Definitely will be coming back!

This place opened on October 29th, and this was my 5th time to eat here.  This place is really Really Delicious.  I have had the Brisket, Pulled Pork, Ribs, and Sausage.  Have not been disappointed!  For the sides I have had the Collard Greens, 8-Cheese Mac & Cheese, Texas Beans,  and Big 8 Beans.  This place is amazing.  Tonight I had a "Secret Menu Item", just have to say the password to get it..."Tornado."  This was INCREDIBLE!  Layers of Brisket, Mac&Cheese, Pickles, Cornbread, Pickled Onion, Cole Slaw, and BBQ Sauce.  Truly Delicious!  It is an appetizer, but the 3 of us had this, and 2 of us could not finish the dinners we purchased.  It is B I G!  The Texas BBQ Sauce has got a great Kick to it, The Memphis is my next favorite, it is nice and spicy!  I have not tried the others.  If you have not been on 47th Ave and tried this place, you got to go.  You can park in the Big John Parking lot across the street.  Amazing!
Big portions/good flavors
We had a big group and they handled it well. Great food and service. I would like to see more bourbon drinks on the menu and some dark beers. Nice decor but how about some blues on the sound system.
Food was outstanding! Brisket was very tender and the Burnt Ends were amazing.  Staff very friendly.  Definitely will go back
Interesting set-up. Meat cart comes to your table. Brisket was very good, ribs ok, not earth-shattering. Overall, not bad. Will probably go back.
Great food!!

We’ve eaten here twice now and absolutely love it! We are picky about our BBQ places and we tried this place a couple days ago and came back the very next night for more! We’ve had the pulled pork, the ribs and the brisket. All were so good and the brisket melts in your mouth. The smoked potato salad and baked beans are my favorite sides. So glad we have a place like this in the Cape now.
Great bbq. The sausage was out of this world. Attentive staff. Everything's freshly made. Went there for the ribs, but they ran out just before we got there. Loved the garlic mac and cheese.
OUTSTANDING  brisket and pulled pork!! Big 8 Beans and coleslaw fantastic!!

OMG we moved from Texas and I was a bit skeptical but this place is legit!  You get to pick your meet table side and they cut it right there. The sides were delicious and the owner came by several times to check on us. We will be back for sure!  Don’t think you can come late and get everything, this is a legit bbq place. Everything is fresh!  When they are out they are out!  I’m dreaming of brisket tonight!  So happy they are here!!!
Absolutely amazing food!! I'm very picky with BBQ, mac n cheese and potato salad and all were delicious!!! Definitely going again!!
We went their today for dinner and it was the BEST BBQ we have ever had hands down.

The food was FABULOUS.  We ordered the Beef Brisket and the 1/2 Chicken - both delicious!  No BBQ sauce required.  The chicken was super moist and tasty.  The sides were also very good.  Staff and owners were very friendly.  Overall we would rate higher than 5 stars if we could.  We will definitely go back and we encourage you to support this local restaurateur!
The food and the service was outstanding! Any time I’m looking for barbecue this will be the place! 👏🏼

I was looking for something special for Veterans Day, and I was not disappointed at all! It pays to read reviews! I ordered a half rack of ribs, and when I picked them up everyone there was so friendly and kind. Since I already paid, the owner gave me a gift card for being a Veteran! and thanked me for my service! I would like to thank them for their amazing service, and absolutely amazing food! Be Back Soon...

The food is delicious!  We ordered a variety of combos and sides so that we could try a bunch.  The brisket, ribs and sausage were SO good.  We also ordered cornbread, Mac and cheese, potato salad, baked beans and coleslaw.  Everything was great!

If you love GARLIC ??? The Garlic Mac and cheese was creamy, ooey gooey goodness !!! Phenomenal !!!! Friendly service with generous portions !!! Definitely  the pulled pork melts in your mouth !!! I will absolutely return to try the rest on the menu !!!!!

Had the privilege of walking into a private sampling of there brisket and all sauces. In my 38 year pursuit of delicious bbq, one has landed in the cape. Now let's talk smoked potato salad, if you having had this, you don't want it any other way. Keep in mind they were closed and still feed me and gave me a tour like I was featured on a cooking network. I see big things come from this small store front with massive flavor. Can't wait to try there bourbon...

This is QUALITY BBQ!! They have their own cooker on premises. Quality meats. Seasoning mild on the meat to accommodate  their array of sauces.  Meats unsurpassed anything local!!!!   Sides were ok. Cornbread was great!!!  Overall, a very appealing pallet! 👍👍👍
Awesome food. Great outdoor seating area. No real mask enforcement inside though.

Stopped in before they actually opened and met the owner Bill, super nice guy, showed me the place couldn't wait to stop in when they actually opened... and I did and what I tried was very good. I had the brisket the pulled pork and the brisket sausage. I'm going to work my way through all the meats and then start doing the sides. They open at 4:00p.m. and when the food is gone I think they go home. So if there's something you want to really try, get there early. I've been in this location before it was Big 8 and they did quite a transformation. They have craft beer, plenty of places to sit inside and out. I really hope that you guys check them out and they succeed. I'll keep you posted as I work my way through the menu.
Absolutely amazing food with great staff! The garlic mac and cheese is the best thing I have ever tasted. I’ve struggled to find good BBQ since moving to Florida and this is definitely my new go-to!
AWESOME service food was delicious

Excellent bbq. Awesome staff. 5 stars all the way. Best bbq I’ve had since been here in Florida. The owner bill was preparing my food and walked me through the menu. Very personable and professional. Highly recommended.
The brisket and pulled chicken is amazing! Ask for Kevin!!

Amazing dinner. Everything we had was awesome. The pulled pork was delicious without sauce but the sauces were amazing, especially the Carolina sauce. 8 cheese mac and cheese was super cheesy and creamy, so good. Definitely will be back.
This was a very pleasant experience! The food was AMAZING! The service from the time that I walked through the door was A+  and Rachel, the bartender is all that and a rack of ribs!

Best Brisket & Ribs I’ve ever had. The greens & mac n cheese were amazing. I can’t say enough good things about the food and the service. Super kid friendly tooo!! Kevin and Bill ( the owners ) were super friendly and really showed that they care about there customers and there name. Super nice guys. Don’t even question it, just go try it out. You won’t regret it. Best down home country cookin!!

This is hands down, THE BEST bbq in SWFL! I’ve been looking for good bbq down here for 5 years and finally found it! I took a risk and ordered it on Uber Eats, thinking it would be more of the same mediocre bbq that we have down here..wrong!! The moistest Turkey, bomb collards, delicious pork. And the cornbread..I’m still swooning over the “icing butter”. This stuff is legit y’all!
Excellent service

I am not such a fan of BBQ places but this is the one to go to! Will definitely be coming back a lot! The brisket and the pull pork are amazing! The smoked potato salad is a must! The Mac & Cheese is very creamy and yummy 😋 The set up is so cool and definitely nice to seat outside too!
Great food, but the setup with in-store service could be better

Excellent food and service!! Had the brisket and pulled pork and both were amazing. Sides of Texas baked beans and 8 cheese Mac and cheese were perfect. Also loved the Texas bbq sauce. Both owners visited our table and are great guys! My new favorite place for barbecue! Thank you

Great BBQ! Tried the brisket and sausage with potato salad and big8 beans. The brisket was so tender and great flavor can cut it with a fork. Would definitely recommend and can’t wait to go back and try the other meats  and sides. The owner Kevin and the staff are super friendly, interactive and great service. ⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️
The Brisket is to die for.  All the side dishes are excellent. I recommend you come early

Was craving BBQ and stumbled across this place on Grubhub .... and holy mother of the bbq gods they absolutely do not disappoint. Pulled pork was delicious and tender , same for the brisket and the ribs were good too, not my favorite but still better than any other restaurant in town ! Large portions enough to share between two people . The sides were great , smoked potato salad was different but in a good way and the 8 cheese Mac and cheese is killer !  You have to try them out , you’ll be happy you did !

Food was delicious!  Texas beans got a little bite.  Collard greens were perfect.  Brisket and Pulled pork were immaculate.  Love the Texas Sauce.  Memphis sauce had nice bite with taste of honey.   Definitely be back.

I had a great time at this place! The BBQ is tender, savory, and delicious. The best in the area hands down. They serve Mr.Tom's liquor additionally, which is made right in Fort Myers and is amazing. The people here are warm, friendly and personable, exactly the kind of people you would expect to specialize in BBQ.
Awesome food

WOW! Exceptional quality and so so tasty!!! Never had bbq taste this good! The atmosphere and service was top notch. Manager checked in was very friendly. The brisket was handcrafted to perfection. The drinks, all excellent local beers. Love the gateway gold. The cocktails and liquor also handcrafted to perfection. Had mr. Tom's 3yr bourban old fashion. Exceptional!! Will recommend this to family and friends!
Food was excellent.  I especially loved the cole slaw and baked beans, which went great with the tender beef brisket.
This is what Cape Coral has been missing. So happy that Big 8 is here.

This is barbecue, service and originality done right. Words can’t explain how much they do things differently and BETTER than the local staples everyone is used to and gloats about when people come from out of town. The food is genuine, not watered down and you won’t find anything like it ANYWHERE in southwest Florida. I’m hoping it doesn’t become too busy for locals but they can always open more locations, which they will! I’ve eaten countless places in SWFL and this is hands down the best place.
The food hear is amazing and the staff is great
Amazing food great people

AWESOME service- go see Rachel she is the best bartender! Brisket and chicken was amazing! Try the Memphis BBQ sauce. Their greens are delicious. Kids had ribs and chicken and also were delish. Two different mac and cheeses that both were great!

Excellent smoked meats, delicious sides and mouthwatering desserts! Bar was extensive and refreshing! From the moment of entering, the Staff were welcoming, attentive and friendly. They want you to relax and enjoy your meal! Highly recommend! Will visit often!

Go try this new BBQ place in Cape Coral. Quality food, great ambiance, kid friendly, and helpful staff. If you love meats, mac & cheese, potato salad, sausages, etc; this is the place for you in SWFL. You’ll love it 😍

WOW!. This BBQ is amazing.  Every BBQ place is going to have to rethink their cooking methods. This beats out rib city, mission bbq and anything else locally.  Eat in, take out or delivery on all major platforms.  There is even a large outside area to enjoy the fresh air.  Opened on October 29th 2020
